    "# b) Potential challenges and considerations unique to the `Legal` domain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b699e775",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. <u>Complex and Specialized Vocabulary:</u>\n",
    "\n",
    "- Legal documents often contain specialized terminology and jargon that may not be common in general language. This can pose challenges in accurately indexing and retrieving relevant documents. \n",
    "\n",
    "    - ex: `adjudicate`, `Appellate Authority`, `deposition`, `non-obstante clause` etc.\n",
    "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "### 2. <u>Long and Complex Sentences: </u>\n",
    "- Legal judgments are known for long, complex sentence structures, which can complicate the process of tokenization and accurate term extraction.\n",
    "\n",
    "    - ex: this is a line in a particular judgement given-\n",
    "    \n",
    "    `These civil revision petitions are filed seeking to assail the order dated 08-06-2007 in I.A. No. 121\n",
    "    of 2007 in O.P. No. 1630 of 2003 and batch, on the file of the XIV Additional Chief Judge, Fast\n",
    "    Track Court, City Civil Court, Hyderabad, wherein the said petitions filed by the petitioners herein\n",
    "    under Order XIV Rule 2 C.P.C., read with Section 19 of the Mirco, Small and Medium Enterprises\n",
    "    Development Act, 2006, (Central Act 27 of 2006)(for short 'the New Act'), praying to decide the\n",
    "    preliminary objection regarding the maintainability of the original petitions without deposit of 75%\n",
    "    of the awarded amount, were dismissed.`\n",
    "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.  <u> Document Length and Structure: </u>\n",
    "- Legal documents are often lengthy and have a structured format (sections, clauses, appendices), which might require a more sophisticated approach to indexing.\n",
    "\n",
    "ex: latest supreme court judgement on Article 370 is 476 pages in length: \n",
    "\n",
    "https://main.sci.gov.in/pdf/LU/article_370.pdf\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4. <u> Need for High Precision and Recall: </u>\n",
    "\n",
    "- In legal research, both high precision (retrieving mostly relevant documents) and high recall (retrieving all relevant documents) are crucial. This often complicates retrieval process.\n",
    "\n",
    "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5. <u> Handling Precedents and Citations:</u> \n",
    "\n",
    "- Legal judgments often reference other judgments or legal texts. Capturing these relationships can be challenging but is crucial for comprehensive information retrieval.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### <u>P.S:</u> All the examples quoted above, except for point 3. are from the corpus of documents we considered for this assignment."
